    "methodology": "999 call answer times are measured from the moment the call connects to the BT operator to the point it is answered by force control room staff. The 10-second target is a service-level agreement. Grade 1 response data is drawn from HMICFRS PEEL inspections and force-level performance reporting; targets vary (15 minutes urban, 20 minutes rural) but national aggregates use a blended 15-minute benchmark. PCSO headcount is full-time equivalent from Home Office Police Workforce Statistics, measured at 31 March each year.",
